# Testing directory contract

Authoritative rules live in **AGENTS.md** (section 2 commands + section 6 canonical tree + **Testing directory contract**). This rule mirrors boundaries for edits under `tests/`.

## Layout

- **`tests/fixtures/`** — Deterministic IDs, emails, user-visible copy strings, static factories. **No** Playwright `Page` / browser APIs. **No** ERP domain workflows.
- **`tests/unit/`** — Vitest. Default **Node**; use `// @vitest-environment jsdom` at the top of a file only when DOM / React Testing Library is required. Prefer naming DOM specs **`*.dom.test.tsx`**. Do **not** introduce Vitest **`projects`** until DOM suites are large enough to justify the split (see AGENTS.md).
- **`tests/e2e/`** — Playwright `*.spec.ts`. Prefer explicit `goto` / `getByRole` / `getByLabel`. Tag stable gates (e.g. `@smoke`). **App Router pages** are exercised here for route-level confidence — not gated by Vitest coverage for now.
- **`tests/e2e/utils/`** — Browser helpers (navigation, auth steps). Import canonical data from **`tests/fixtures`**, do not duplicate magic IDs/copy. Avoid deep `test.extend` pyramids.

## Coverage (V8)

- **`pnpm test:ci`** / **`pnpm test:coverage`** run Vitest with **`@vitest/coverage-v8`**. Reports: **`.artifacts/coverage/`** (`coverage-summary.json`, `lcov.info`, text).
- **IAM-sensitive shared modules** (`lib/auth/**/*.shared.ts`, **`lib/auth/callback-path.ts`**) must meet **≥ 95%** coverage (lines, statements, branches, functions) — enforced in [`vitest.config.ts`](vitest.config.ts).
- **Global executed coverage** is **ratcheted** from the current baseline (~mid-60%) toward **80%**. Do **not** enable **`coverage.all: true`** until the repo has enough intentional unit breadth — untouched files must not count as 0% prematurely.

## React Testing Library

Use RTL only for small client islands: auth UI, forms, a11y, OTP/password toggle, loading/error states. Keep pure **`lib/**`** tests Node-only.

## Artifacts

- CI JUnit and similar outputs go under **`.artifacts/`** (gitignored). Do not commit reports.

## Playwright URL

- Default Playwright base URL is **`http://127.0.0.1:3001`** with **`next start`** so **`pnpm dev`** can stay on **3000**. Override with **`PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL`** or **`BASE_URL`**. Full contract: **AGENTS.md** testing subsection.
